Who am I?


Since most of the content on this site is focused around me professionally, I'd like to offer this small section about me personally for those that would like to get to know me a bit more. I grew up in Indiana the first 20 years of my life, and currently reside in Tampa, FL. I am a pretty avid sports fan. I played baseball and golf growing up, and still play golf regualry to this day. However, I enjoy watching sports as much as I do playing them. I am particullary fond of Chicago sports teams such as the Cubs, Blackhawks, Bears, and Bulls. Going over to my grandparents house during summer afternoons to eat PB&J and watch the Cubs are some of my favorite childhood memories. Like most guys in their twenties that are in this field, I do also enjoy playing video games. However, what I most enjoy about them is that they have been a great outlet to keep connected with my friends I still have back in Indiana. I'm hardly a chef, but I do enjoy cooking and even more so eating. I would probably have to say I love Thai food the most, but I will try just about anything once. Outside of that, my typical post-work day includes exercising, reading, and even working on side-projects such as this very site here.
